The leadership of All Farmers Association of Nigeria (AFAN) and the Miyetti Allah Cattle Breeders Association of Nigeria (MACBAN) have resolved to work together to end the farmer-herder crisis in parts of the country. In a resolution issued in Abuja yesterday and read by AFAN President, Kabiru Ibrahim, the associations said peace is imperative for the growth of agriculture saying “We agreed to work together to expose the criminals from among us to ensure peace and prosperity in Nigeria. The resolution also noted that “the real herdsmen do not carry AK 47, do not raze a whole settlement but desires peace to harness his pastoral activities.”